LEVEL ORDER TRAVERSAL OF A BINARY TREE

You are given a binary tree. Your task is to print the level order traversal of its nodes. In level order traversal, nodes are visited level by level from left to right.

TASK

Print the nodes of the binary tree level by level.

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer N
N is the number of nodes in the binary tree

The next (N - 1) lines describe the edges of the tree
Each line contains three values:
pi ci Ri

where
pi is the parent node value
ci is the child node value
Ri represents the relationship
L means ci is the left child of pi
R means ci is the right child of pi

OUTPUT FORMAT

Print the level order traversal of the tree
Each level should be printed on a new line
Nodes in the same level should be space-separated

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ N ≤ 10000
1 ≤ pi, ci ≤ 100000
Ri is either L or R
All node values are distinct

SAMPLE INPUT

5
1 2 L
1 3 R
3 4 L
3 5 R

SAMPLE OUTPUT

1
2 3
4 5

EXPLANATION

The tree is traversed level by level
First level contains node 1
Second level contains nodes 2 and 3
Third level contains nodes 4 and 5

==========================
class Solution {
    public void levelOrderTraversal(Node root) {
        if(root == null) return;
        Queue<Node> q = new LinkedList<>();

        q.add(root);
        q.add(null);

        while(!q.isEmpty()){

            Node curr = q.poll();

            if(curr == null){
                System.out.println();

                if(!q.isEmpty())
                    q.add(null);
            }
            else{

                System.out.print(curr.val + " ");

                if(curr.left != null)
                    q.add(curr.left);

                if(curr.right != null)
                    q.add(curr.right);
            }
        }
    }
}
